title: Bug 110566 - Wrong data set result returned when an invalid filter expression is set for row[0]
description: When setting a filter expression like "row[0] equals to 0", the result set is not as expected. It either returns the wrong data set or just returns a null result set.
OB: The data set result is incorrect or null when an invalid filter expression is set for row[0].
EB: An error message should be displayed to indicate the invalid filter expression.
SR:
To reproduce the issue: 
1. Set a filter expression like "row[0] equals to 0" for row[0]. 
2. Observe the result set and verify if it is incorrect or null. 
3. Check for the presence of an error message indicating the invalid filter expression.
